<title>USA: Japan proposes bigger Asian role in Africa.</title>
<headline>Japan proposes bigger Asian role in Africa.</headline>
<dateline>DENVER 1997-06-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto called at the Group of Seven summit on Saturday for Asian nations to play a greater role in helping develop African economies, Japanese officials said.</p>
<p>He proposed that Japan host a conference in Okinawa next year for Asian countries that have recently begun extending help to Africa, they added.</p>
<p>Japan, the only Asian member of the G7, has made special efforts to ensure the region is not neglected in the Denver discussions, the officials said.</p>
<p>They said Japanese leaders raised regional concerns like in Burma and Cambodia, the Korean peninsula and the future of Hong Kong after it reverts to China on July 1.</p>
